&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>shelly bthome list</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/bthome/list/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/bthome/list/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-bthome-list"&gt;shelly bthome list&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;List BTHome devices&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="synopsis"&gt;Synopsis&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;List all BTHome devices connected to a Shelly gateway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BTHome is a Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) protocol for sensors and devices.
Shelly BLU sensors (motion, door/window, button) connect to a gateway
device that collects their readings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shows configured BTHomeDevice components with their current status,
signal strength (RSSI), battery level, and last update time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use &amp;lsquo;shelly bthome add&amp;rsquo; to discover and pair new devices.
Use &amp;lsquo;shelly bthome sensors&amp;rsquo; to view sensor readings.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>shelly bthome remove</title><link>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/bthome/remove/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tj-smith47.github.io/shelly-cli/docs/commands/bthome/remove/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="shelly-bthome-remove"&gt;shelly bthome remove&lt;/h2&gt;
